data.title: Malawi Rural population, percent - data, chart
data.meta_description: Malawi: Rural population, percent of total population: The latest value from 2023 is 81.72 percent, a decline from 82.02 percent in 2022. In comparison, the world average is 38.64 percent, based on data from 196 countries. Historically, the average for Malawi from 1960 to 2023 is 88.43 percent. The minimum value, 81.72 percent, was reached in 2023 while the maximum of 95.61 percent was recorded in 1960.
